    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-12T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-12T20:00:00-05:00" n="225"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1190.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-12T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 9, 9 p.m. and January 11, 10 a.m. Insular Bureau will today instruct
                    Receiver General to place additional $20,000 of Dominican Government’s
                    percentage of customs collections at its disposal. This should render
                    momentarily unnecessary loan from Royal Bank of Canada. John Gray, attorney of
                    Banco Nacional de <pb facs="0314" n="198" xml:id="pg_198"/> San Domingo, assured
                    Department Saturday that bank would today complete payment first $20,000 and not
                    withhold its percentage from second advance of like amount. Discreetly endeavor
                    to procure itemized list of small loans already made with statement as to terms
                    upon which each was negotiated and discourage further loans on disadvantageous
                    terms. It is expected forty thousand dollars already advanced will cover
                    Dominican Government’s daily needs including the 15th instant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
